It gives me great pleasure to announce the first 'Community Evening with STEAM' organised by the Friends of STEAM, a parent, teacher and student body of Viewbank College, on May 29th 2018 at Viewbank College, Warren Road, Rosanna, Melbourne from 7 pm to 8 pm. We are thrilled to have our alumni Alex Kingsbury, Managing Director of Additive Economics and former Director of ‘Lab 22’ at CSIRO to start this community engagement initiative with her Keynote “3D Printing Our Future - How new technology will change education, jobs and the economy".

This initiative mirrors our school vision of bringing together industry, academia, schools and the wider community in developing a strong understanding of STEAM and its implications on our future. We look forward to your participation and support of this initiative.

Please confirm your attendance by booking through the following link:

www.trybooking.com/VOWH

Limited seats . Gold coin donations at the door

#Alex Kingbury
